<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
<meta charset="UTF-8">
<meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0, maximum-scale=1.0, user-scalable=no">
<title>EP Teacher Questionnaire — EYFS &amp; Early Needs</title>
<link href="https://fonts.googleapis.com/css2?family=Nunito:wght@400;600;700;800&family=Lora:ital,wght@0,600;1,400&display=swap" rel="stylesheet">
<style>
:root{
  --teal:#1a5f7a;--teal-lt:#e6f3f8;--teal-dk:#0f3d52;
  --amber:#c46b1a;--amber-lt:#fdf3e6;
  --rose:#b5333c;--rose-lt:#fdf0f0;
  --navy:#1a2744;--slate:#4a5568;--mid:#6b7280;
  --border:#dde3ed;--bg:#f5f7fa;--white:#fff;
  --fh:'Lora',Georgia,serif;--fb:'Nunito',-apple-system,sans-serif;
  --r:16px;--sh:0 2px 20px rgba(27,45,80,.09)
}
*{box-sizing:border-box;margin:0;padding:0}
body{background:var(--bg);font-family:var(--fb);color:var(--navy);font-size:16px;line-height:1.65;-webkit-tap-highlight-color:transparent}
input,textarea,select,button{font-family:var(--fb);font-size:15px}

.hdr{background:var(--teal-dk);padding:14px 20px;display:flex;align-items:center;justify-content:space-between;position:sticky;top:0;z-index:200;box-shadow:0 3px 16px rgba(0,0,0,.3)}
.hdr h1{font-family:var(--fh);color:#fff;font-size:16px;line-height:1.2;font-style:italic}
.hdr .sub{color:rgba(255,255,255,.5);font-size:11px;text-transform:uppercase;letter-spacing:.07em;margin-top:2px;font-style:normal}
.pct{background:rgba(255,255,255,.15);color:#fff;border-radius:20px;padding:4px 10px;font-size:12px;font-weight:700}

.svb{background:var(--teal);color:#fff;text-align:center;padding:7px;font-size:13px;font-weight:600;transition:opacity .4s;height:34px}
.svb.hidden{opacity:0;pointer-events:none}

.snav{display:flex;gap:6px;padding:10px 14px;overflow-x:auto;background:#fff;border-bottom:1px solid var(--border);scrollbar-width:none;-webkit-overflow-scrolling:touch}
.snav::-webkit-scrollbar{display:none}
.npill{flex:0 0 auto;padding:6px 13px;border-radius:20px;font-size:12.5px;font-weight:600;border:1.5px solid var(--border);background:#fff;color:var(--slate);cursor:pointer;white-space:nowrap;transition:all .15s}
.npill.act{background:var(--teal-dk);border-color:var(--teal-dk);color:#fff}
.npill.vis{border-color:var(--teal);color:var(--teal)}

.fw{max-width:720px;margin:0 auto;padding:16px 16px 60px}

.sh{margin:22px 0 14px}
.sbadge{display:inline-flex;align-items:center;background:var(--teal-dk);color:#fff;font-size:11px;font-weight:700;letter-spacing:.07em;text-transform:uppercase;padding:3px 10px;border-radius:4px;margin-bottom:8px}
.sh h2{font-family:var(--fh);font-size:21px;margin-bottom:4px}
.sh p{font-size:14px;color:var(--slate)}

.card{background:#fff;border-radius:var(--r);padding:20px;margin-bottom:12px;box-shadow:var(--sh)}
.card label{display:block;font-size:14px;font-weight:600;color:var(--navy);margin-bottom:7px}
.card input[type=text],.card input[type=email],.card input[type=tel],.card input[type=number],.card select,.card textarea{width:100%;padding:11px 14px;border:1.5px solid var(--border);border-radius:9px;font-size:15px;color:var(--navy);background:var(--bg);transition:border-color .15s}
.card input:focus,.card select:focus,.card textarea:focus{outline:none;border-color:var(--teal);background:#fff}
.card textarea{min-height:76px;resize:vertical}
.fr{display:grid;grid-template-columns:1fr 1fr;gap:12px}
.fr3{display:grid;grid-template-columns:1fr 1fr 1fr;gap:12px}
@media(max-width:500px){.fr{grid-template-columns:1fr}.fr3{grid-template-columns:1fr}}
.hint{font-size:12px;color:var(--mid);font-style:italic;margin-bottom:8px;margin-top:-2px}

.rg{display:flex;flex-direction:column;gap:7px}
.ro{display:flex;align-items:center;gap:10px;padding:10px 14px;border:1.5px solid var(--border);border-radius:9px;cursor:pointer;font-size:14px;transition:all .12s}
.ro:hover{border-color:var(--teal);background:var(--teal-lt)}
.ro.sel{border-color:var(--teal);background:var(--teal-lt);font-weight:600}
.ro input{accent-color:var(--teal);width:17px;height:17px;flex-shrink:0}
.rg-inline{display:flex;flex-direction:row;flex-wrap:wrap;gap:8px;margin-top:8px}
.rg-inline .ro{flex:0 0 auto;width:auto}
.cg{display:grid;grid-template-columns:1fr 1fr;gap:7px}
@media(max-width:480px){.cg{grid-template-columns:1fr}}
.co{display:flex;align-items:center;gap:8px;padding:9px 12px;border:1.5px solid var(--border);border-radius:8px;cursor:pointer;font-size:13.5px;transition:all .12s}
.co:hover{border-color:var(--teal);background:var(--teal-lt)}
.co.sel{border-color:var(--teal);background:var(--teal-lt)}
.co input{accent-color:var(--teal);width:16px;height:16px;flex-shrink:0}

.qb{background:#fff;border-radius:var(--r);padding:18px 20px;margin-bottom:10px;box-shadow:var(--sh)}
.qb .q{font-size:15px;font-weight:600;color:var(--navy);margin-bottom:6px}
.qb .qh{font-size:12px;color:var(--mid);font-style:italic;margin-bottom:8px}
.qb textarea{width:100%;padding:11px 14px;border:1.5px solid var(--border);border-radius:9px;font-size:15px;color:var(--navy);background:var(--bg);min-height:76px;resize:vertical}
.qb textarea:focus{outline:none;border-color:var(--teal);background:#fff}

.tsec{background:#fff;border-radius:var(--r);margin-bottom:12px;overflow:visible;box-shadow:var(--sh)}
.tttl{background:var(--teal-lt);padding:11px 16px;font-size:14px;font-weight:700;color:var(--teal-dk);border-bottom:1px solid #a8d4e3;border-radius:var(--r) var(--r) 0 0}
.tchdr{display:grid;grid-template-columns:1fr 1fr;background:var(--bg);border-bottom:1px solid var(--border)}
.tchdr span{padding:7px 14px;font-size:11.5px;font-weight:700;text-transform:uppercase;letter-spacing:.06em}
.tchdr .shdr{color:var(--teal);border-right:1px solid var(--border)}
.tchdr .dhdr{color:var(--rose)}
.tbody{display:grid;grid-template-columns:1fr 1fr}
.tcol{display:flex;flex-direction:column}
.tcol.sc{border-right:1px solid var(--border)}
.ti{display:flex;align-items:flex-start;gap:9px;padding:10px 14px;border-bottom:1px solid var(--border);cursor:pointer;transition:background .1s;font-size:13.5px;line-height:1.4}
.ti:last-child{border-bottom:none}
.ti:hover{background:var(--bg)}
.ti input[type=checkbox]{flex-shrink:0;width:17px;height:17px;margin-top:2px;accent-color:var(--teal)}
.tcol.dc .ti input[type=checkbox]{accent-color:var(--rose)}

.dex{display:none;padding:12px 14px 14px;background:#fff8f8;border-top:1px solid #f5cfc9;border-bottom:1px solid #f5cfc9}
.dex.open{display:block}
.dex .dlbl{font-size:13px;font-weight:700;color:var(--rose);margin-bottom:5px;display:block}
.dex textarea{width:100%;padding:10px 12px;border:1.5px solid #f5cfc9;border-radius:8px;font-size:14px;color:var(--navy);background:#fff;min-height:68px;resize:vertical}
.dex textarea:focus{outline:none;border-color:var(--rose)}
.dex .egrid{display:grid;grid-template-columns:1fr 1fr;gap:10px}
@media(max-width:520px){.dex .egrid{grid-template-columns:1fr}}

.tnotes{padding:12px 16px;background:var(--bg);border-top:1px solid var(--border);border-radius:0 0 var(--r) var(--r)}
.tnotes label{font-size:13px;font-weight:600;color:var(--slate);margin-bottom:6px;display:block}
.tnotes textarea{width:100%;padding:10px 12px;border:1.5px solid var(--border);border-radius:8px;font-size:14px;color:var(--navy);background:#fff;min-height:64px;resize:vertical}
.tnotes textarea:focus{outline:none;border-color:var(--teal)}

.obox{background:var(--amber-lt);border:1.5px solid #e8b580;border-radius:var(--r);padding:18px 20px;margin-bottom:12px}
.obox h3{font-family:var(--fh);font-size:16px;color:var(--amber);margin-bottom:4px}
.obox p{font-size:13px;color:var(--slate);margin-bottom:12px}
.oi{margin-bottom:10px}
.oi label{font-size:13.5px;font-weight:600;color:var(--navy);margin-bottom:5px;display:block}
.oi textarea{width:100%;padding:10px 12px;border:1.5px solid #e8b580;border-radius:8px;font-size:14px;color:var(--navy);background:#fff;min-height:60px;resize:vertical}
.oi textarea:focus{outline:none;border-color:var(--amber)}
.oi textarea::placeholder{color:#c8a888;font-style:italic}

.prt{background:#fff;border-radius:var(--r);box-shadow:var(--sh);overflow:hidden;margin-bottom:12px}
.prr{display:flex;align-items:center;gap:12px;padding:12px 16px;border-bottom:1px solid var(--border);font-size:14px}
.prr:last-child{border-bottom:none}
.prr input[type=checkbox]{width:18px;height:18px;flex-shrink:0;accent-color:var(--navy)}
.prrl{flex:1;cursor:pointer}
.prrs{margin-left:auto;display:flex;align-items:center;gap:6px;font-size:13px;color:var(--mid);flex-shrink:0}
.prrs select{padding:4px 8px;border:1.5px solid var(--border);border-radius:6px;font-size:13px;color:var(--navy);background:var(--bg)}

.iw{max-width:560px;margin:40px auto;padding:16px}
.ic{background:#fff;border-radius:22px;padding:32px 28px;box-shadow:var(--sh)}
.ic h2{font-family:var(--fh);font-size:24px;margin-bottom:4px}
.ic .st{color:var(--mid);font-size:14px;margin-bottom:20px}
.infobox{background:var(--teal-lt);border-left:4px solid var(--teal);border-radius:0 12px 12px 0;padding:15px 17px;margin:18px 0;font-size:14px;color:var(--navy)}
.infobox strong{display:block;color:var(--teal-dk);font-size:12px;text-transform:uppercase;letter-spacing:.06em;margin-bottom:5px}
.infobox p{margin-bottom:7px}
.infobox p:last-child{margin-bottom:0}
.resbox{background:var(--amber-lt);border:1.5px solid var(--amber);border-radius:10px;padding:14px 16px;margin:14px 0;font-size:14px}
.resbox strong{color:var(--amber);display:block;font-size:12px;text-transform:uppercase;letter-spacing:.06em;margin-bottom:4px}

.btn{display:block;width:100%;padding:14px 20px;border-radius:10px;border:none;font-size:15px;font-weight:700;cursor:pointer;text-align:center;transition:transform .1s}
.btn:active{transform:scale(.98)}
.btp{background:var(--teal);color:#fff;margin-bottom:10px;box-shadow:0 4px 14px rgba(26,95,122,.35)}
.bts{background:#fff;color:var(--navy);border:1.5px solid var(--border);margin-bottom:10px}
.btf{background:var(--teal-dk);color:#fff;box-shadow:0 4px 14px rgba(15,61,82,.35)}
.bte{background:#2c7a2c;color:#fff;box-shadow:0 4px 14px rgba(44,122,44,.35);margin-bottom:10px}
.nbs{display:flex;gap:10px;margin-top:24px}
.nbs .btn{flex:1}

.dw{max-width:560px;margin:40px auto;padding:16px;text-align:center}
.dc{background:#fff;border-radius:22px;padding:28px;box-shadow:var(--sh)}
.dc h2{font-family:var(--fh);font-size:22px;margin-bottom:10px}
.dc p{color:var(--slate);font-size:14px;margin-bottom:12px}
.rpre{background:var(--bg);border:1px solid var(--border);border-radius:10px;padding:18px;text-align:left;font-size:12.5px;line-height:1.7;white-space:pre-wrap;max-height:380px;overflow-y:auto;margin:14px 0;color:var(--navy)}

.sinote{background:var(--teal-lt);border-radius:10px;padding:12px 16px;font-size:13.5px;color:var(--navy);margin-bottom:14px;border:1px solid #a8d4e3}
.teach-note{background:#fffbf0;border:1.5px solid #e8c96a;border-radius:10px;padding:12px 16px;font-size:13.5px;color:var(--navy);margin-bottom:14px}

.attbar-bg{height:20px;background:#e8edf5;border-radius:10px;overflow:hidden;margin:10px 0 4px}
.attbar{height:100%;border-radius:10px;transition:width .4s;background:var(--teal)}
.attbar.amber{background:#e07b2e}
.attbar.red{background:var(--rose)}
.attlabel{font-size:12px;color:var(--mid);text-align:right}

.email-input{display:flex;gap:8px;margin-bottom:12px}
.email-input input{flex:1;padding:11px 14px;border:1.5px solid var(--border);border-radius:9px;font-size:15px;color:var(--navy);background:var(--bg)}
.email-input input:focus{outline:none;border-color:var(--teal)}
</style>
</head>
<body>
<div id="app"></div>
<script>
const SK='ep_eyfs_teacher_v1';

const SECS=[
  {id:'det',t:'Setting Details',i:'🏫'},
  {id:'bg',t:'Background',i:'📋'},
  {id:'att',t:'Attendance',i:'📅'},
  {id:'sup',t:'Support in Place',i:'🤝'},
  {id:'pri',t:'Main Concerns',i:'⭐'},
  {id:'phy',t:'A: Physical & Sensory',i:'🏃'},
  {id:'com',t:'B: Communication',i:'💬'},
  {id:'sem',t:'C: Emotional & Social',i:'❤️'},
  {id:'cog',t:'D: Learning & Play',i:'🧩'},
  {id:'cv',t:"Child's Voice",i:'🗣️'},
  {id:'tv',t:'Teacher Views',i:'👩‍🏫'},
];

const DH={
  phys_h2_d:['e.g., squints at the board, avoids visual tasks, eyes water frequently','e.g., optician referral made, larger print resources, seated closer to board'],
  phys_h3_d:['e.g., does not respond when called across the room, mishears instructions','e.g., audiology referral, face child when speaking, reduce background noise'],
  phys_h4_d:['e.g., needs inhaler before PE, medication administered by named adult','e.g., individual healthcare plan in place, named adult manages medication'],
  phys_s1_d:['e.g., refuses sand, paint, playdough, grass — distress at any messy activity','e.g., introduce textures gradually, alternatives offered, OT referral made'],
  phys_s2_d:['e.g., distressed by bright lighting in hall, covers eyes, refuses certain rooms','e.g., dimmer lighting where possible, seated away from windows'],
  phys_s3_d:['e.g., gags at cooking smells, cleaning products, other children\'s food at lunch','e.g., unscented cleaning products, eats separately, pre-warned before smell events'],
  phys_s4_d:['e.g., covers ears at assembly, hand dryers, fire alarms — cannot settle afterwards','e.g., ear defenders provided, pre-warned before loud events, quiet retreat available'],
  phys_s5_d:['e.g., constant spinning, mouthing objects, crashing into furniture deliberately','e.g., movement breaks scheduled, sensory diet in place, OT referral made'],
  phys_f1_d:['e.g., cannot hold a pencil functionally, cannot manage simple puzzles or jigsaws','e.g., adapted tools, OT referral, pre-writing programme, larger resources'],
  phys_f2_d:['e.g., refuses all mark-making, very immature grip, avoids all pencil/pen activities','e.g., chunky crayons, finger paint, OT referral'],
  phys_f3_d:['e.g., needs full adult help to dress/undress for PE, cannot manage coat zip','e.g., velcro shoes, extra time for changing, adult support for PE'],
  phys_f4_d:['e.g., drops resources, cannot pick up counters, knocks everything over','e.g., larger resources, tray to contain items, adult support for fine motor tasks'],
  phys_g1_d:['e.g., falls frequently on flat ground, very unsteady on stairs, trips constantly','e.g., hand-holding for stairs, physio referral, trip hazards removed'],
  phys_g2_d:['e.g., refuses all outdoor PE, sits out consistently, avoids playground equipment','e.g., physio referral, adapted activities, gentle encouragement with key adult'],
  phys_g3_d:['e.g., cannot throw or catch at all, avoids all ball games, no targeting ability','e.g., large/soft balls, short distances, OT/physio referral'],
  phys_g4_d:['e.g., constantly bumps into peers and furniture, no body awareness','e.g., body-awareness activities, clear space, OT/physio referral'],
  phys_d2_d:['e.g., eats only 2-4 foods at lunch, extreme distress at smell/sight of other food','e.g., eats separately, no pressure, SALT or dietitian referral'],
  phys_d3_d:['e.g., falling asleep in sessions, unable to concentrate due to exhaustion','e.g., morning activities prioritised, sleep clinic referral discussed with parents'],
  phys_d4_d:['e.g., accidents frequently in setting, not yet reliably toilet trained','e.g., toileting programme in place, continence nurse referral, prompted visits'],
  phys_d5_d:['e.g., needs full adult dressing/undressing, no independence with any clothing','e.g., velcro/elastic clothing, step-by-step practice, OT referral'],
  phys_safe1_d:['e.g., runs out of room without warning, no response to stop/wait/no','e.g., visual stop sign, physical barriers near exits, close adult supervision'],
  phys_safe2_d:['e.g., climbs dangerously, runs into others, unaware of hazards outdoors','e.g., gated outdoor area, 1:1 supervision outdoors, designated safe zone'],
  phys_safe3_d:['e.g., wanders away on visits, no road awareness, does not hold hands','e.g., 1:1 adult on all trips, high-vis vest, risk assessment updated'],
  phys_safe4_d:['e.g., goes with strangers, no concern about who they follow','e.g., social stories about safety, safeguarding plan, parental alert system'],
  phys_safe5_d:['e.g., runs into roads, does not understand traffic or pedestrian crossings','e.g., hands held near all roads, road safety teaching with trusted adult'],
  comm_s1_d:['e.g., uses fewer than 50 words, communicates mainly through behaviour or pointing','e.g., SALT referral, PECS/AAC in use, Makaton, total communication approach'],
  comm_s2_d:['e.g., uses no words, only vocalisations or reaches to communicate needs','e.g., SALT referral urgently, respond to all communication attempts, model language'],
  comm_s3_d:['e.g., cannot request pain, hunger, discomfort or help verbally or non-verbally','e.g., SALT referral, teach basic requesting via objects/pictures/signs'],
  comm_s4_d:['e.g., does not understand get your coat or sit down without physical prompt','e.g., simplify to single words with gesture alongside, SALT referral'],
  comm_s5_d:['e.g., does not understand no, stop or basic safety language','e.g., simple consistent vocabulary, physical prompt alongside word, SALT referral'],
  comm_s6_d:['e.g., only functional requests, no conversational exchange or back-and-forth','e.g., intensive interaction, responsive communication approach, SALT involvement'],
  comm_s7_d:['e.g., does not point to share interest, no joint attention with adults in setting','e.g., SALT, autism assessment consideration, intensive interaction, follow child\'s lead'],
  comm_s8_d:['e.g., speech very unclear even to familiar staff, approximations only','e.g., SALT referral for speech sound work, model correct form back, do not correct'],
  comm_l1_d:['e.g., no response to name called from close range or familiar adults','e.g., hearing test, get to eye level, touch to gain attention, SALT referral'],
  comm_l2_d:['e.g., does not respond to name being called, delayed or very inconsistent','e.g., ensure hearing tested, use name plus touch, SALT review'],
  comm_l3_d:['e.g., cannot follow sit down or get your coat without physical demonstration','e.g., one-word instruction with gesture, physical prompt, visual schedule, SALT'],
  comm_l4_d:['e.g., instructions with two steps not followed even with known language','e.g., one instruction at a time, gesture alongside, visual cue cards'],
  comm_l5_d:['e.g., cannot identify familiar objects, people or actions by name','e.g., consistent naming, SALT support, visual labelling of environment'],
  comm_l6_d:['e.g., covers ears, cries, or cannot function in busy or noisy group activities','e.g., ear defenders, quieter space, small group activities first'],
  comm_p1_d:['e.g., no eye contact at all, even in highly motivating play situations','e.g., do not force eye contact, build through play, autism assessment consideration'],
  comm_p2_d:['e.g., no interest in peers, moves away when others approach','e.g., supported parallel play, introduce gradually with motivating activities'],
  comm_p3_d:['e.g., no joint attention, does not look to adult when something interesting happens','e.g., build through favourite activities, follow child\'s lead, SALT support'],
  comm_p4_d:['e.g., does not respond to social games, clapping, turn-taking, peekaboo','e.g., intensive interaction, start with physical/sensory play, follow child\'s interests'],
  sem_e1_d:['e.g., cannot be settled by any adult in setting, extreme distress daily','e.g., consistent key adult, predictable routine, safe space, consider referral'],
  sem_e2_d:['e.g., flat affect, little emotional range, no smiling or apparent enjoyment','e.g., playful engagement, safeguarding review, attachment history, CAMHS consideration'],
  sem_e3_d:['e.g., once upset takes 30+ mins to calm, nothing available helps in setting','e.g., regulation toolkit, quiet safe space, co-regulation, OT/CAMHS referral'],
  sem_e4_d:['e.g., does not respond to praise, stickers, verbal encouragement or rewards in setting','e.g., explore motivators, try various reward styles, autism assessment consideration'],
  sem_e5_d:['e.g., no warning signs — escalates from calm to extreme crisis instantly','e.g., close observation of subtle cues, proactive regulation, CAMHS referral'],
  sem_e6_d:['e.g., no attachment to any adult in setting — treats all adults identically or avoids all','e.g., key person approach, slow trust-building, safeguarding and attachment review'],
  sem_e7_d:['e.g., extreme distress if timetable changes — even minor variations cause meltdown','e.g., visual timetable, advance warning, transition object, autism assessment'],
  sem_e8_d:['e.g., extreme tantrums lasting 45+ minutes, very difficult to de-escalate in setting','e.g., identify triggers, safe space, co-regulation, consistent response, CAMHS referral'],
  sem_s1_d:['e.g., cannot tolerate other children near, bites, hits or withdraws completely','e.g., parallel play at distance, gated safe space, gradual reduction in distance'],
  sem_s2_d:['e.g., actively distressed when peers approach, moves to edges of all spaces','e.g., start with one trusted peer, build very slowly, autism assessment consideration'],
  sem_s3_d:['e.g., no awareness when others are upset or hurt in setting','e.g., label others\' emotions consistently, emotion picture work, SALT/autism assessment'],
  sem_s4_d:['e.g., extreme distress over any shared resource, even with adult support','e.g., own set of resources, gradual turn-taking introduction, start with preferred items'],
  sem_s5_d:['e.g., ignores or laughs at peers\' distress — no apparent empathy shown','e.g., emotion coaching, model empathy, social stories, SALT support'],
  cog_p1_d:['e.g., refuses sand, water, paint, playdough — extreme distress at messy play','e.g., gradual desensitisation, dry sand alternatives, OT referral'],
  cog_p2_d:['e.g., refuses outdoor area entirely, avoids all equipment, stays at door','e.g., gentle encouragement, favourite toy taken outside, adult stays close'],
  cog_p3_d:['e.g., cannot do a 4-piece inset puzzle, throws pieces, gives up immediately','e.g., simpler shape sorters first, model together, break into small steps'],
  cog_p4_d:['e.g., no imaginative play — does not feed a doll, drive a car or pretend','e.g., model play alongside, follow child\'s lead, SALT/autism assessment'],
  cog_p5_d:['e.g., refuses all drawing, painting, colouring, craft — avoids mark-making entirely','e.g., finger paint, chunky tools, paint in sand, OT if needed'],
  cog_p6_d:['e.g., refuses to join in songs, rhymes or music — distressed or completely disengaged','e.g., child\'s favourite sounds/songs, low-demand joining, instruments'],
