  <p>For children who cannot verbally communicate their views, this section should be based on careful observation of the child's behaviour, preferences and responses in your setting. Your observations are the child's voice.</p></div>
  <div class="teach-note">💡 <strong>For non-verbal or minimally verbal children:</strong> Think about what the child <em>shows you</em> — where they go when they enter the room, what they reach for, what makes them engage or disengage, what consistently produces a positive response, and what triggers distress. All of this is their voice.</div>
  ${qb('cv_likes','What does the child seem to most enjoy or seek out in the setting?','e.g., always goes to the water tray first, seeks out spinning toys, engages most with music activities')}
  ${qb('cv_dislikes','What does the child seem to dislike or avoid in the setting?','e.g., refuses outdoor PE, distressed by the dinner hall, leaves carpet immediately, avoids all messy play')}
  ${qb('cv_people','Which staff or peers does the child seem most comfortable with or drawn to?','e.g., seeks out key person consistently, responds well to calm adult voice, ignores all peers')}
  ${qb('cv_calm','What helps the child feel calm, settled and ready to engage in the setting?','e.g., a specific toy at arrival, a particular routine, being near a window, movement before carpet time')}
  ${qb('cv_setting_feel','How does the child appear to feel about coming into the setting?','e.g., arrives distressed every session, settles within 10 minutes, appears indifferent to transitions')}
  ${qb('cv_motivated','What motivates the child — what will they work for or seek out in learning?','e.g., bubbles, specific books, iPad, physical activity, praise from key person, certain songs')}
  ${qb('cv_proud','What can the child do that they appear proud of or that you have noted as a strength?','e.g., exceptional memory for vehicle names, can operate the tablet independently, very nurturing with animals')}
  ${qb('cv_future','As a professional, what do you hope this child will experience and achieve?','e.g., to make a connection with one peer, to communicate a basic need independently, to access learning with less distress')}`;
}

function rTV(){
  return`<div class="sh"><span class="sbadge">7. Teacher/Setting Views</span><h2>👩‍🏫 Your Professional Views &amp; Observations</h2>
  <p>This section is your professional contribution to the EP assessment. Please be as specific, evidence-based and honest as possible. The EP relies on your knowledge of this child in the setting.</p></div>
  ${qb('tv_str','What do you see as this child\'s greatest strengths and areas of progress?','e.g., has begun to make eye contact with key person, shows genuine enjoyment of music, is beginning to request using PECS')}
  ${qb('tv_con','What are your biggest professional concerns about this child right now?','e.g., has not spoken a single word in the setting despite 6 months; self-harms when distressed; no functional communication at age 4')}
  ${qb('tv_compare','How does this child\'s development compare to others of the same age in your setting?','e.g., working approximately 18 months behind peers across all areas; communication is at 12-month level; play is largely solitary')}
  ${qb('tv_progress','What progress has the child made since joining the setting?','e.g., has gone from arriving in distress daily to settling within 5 minutes; can now make one-word requests using PECS; recognises key person')}
  ${qb('tv_typical','How does the child\'s presentation vary across the day/week/term?','e.g., better in the mornings, worse after weekends; more dysregulated at start of term; responds better 1:1 than in groups')}
  ${qb('tv_home','How does the child\'s behaviour/presentation in the setting compare to what parents report at home?','e.g., parents report child speaks in full sentences at home but is completely non-verbal in setting; parents say no behaviour issues at home')}
  ${qb('tv_triggers','What typically triggers distress, dysregulation or challenging behaviour in setting?','e.g., transition between activities, unexpected noise, another child taking their toy, change to usual routine')}
  ${qb('tv_strategies','What does the child respond well to in terms of strategies and approaches?','e.g., advance warnings, visual supports, 1:1 adult, familiar routine, sensory regulation before learning activities')}
  ${qb('tv_concerns_send','In your professional view, what areas of SEND does this child have, and how significant are these?','e.g., in my professional view this child has significant communication and language needs alongside sensory processing differences that require specialist assessment')}
  ${qb('tv_next','What do you believe this child needs next that the setting cannot currently provide without additional funding or specialist support?','e.g., intensive specialist SALT input, a reduced-ratio environment, specialist nursery placement, OT sensory assessment and programme')}
  ${qb('tv_ehcp','Why does this child need an EHCP (if applicable), and what would it enable?','e.g., the child requires significantly more than the setting can fund from its notional SEND budget; an EHCP would enable 1:1 specialist support throughout the day')}
  ${qb('tv_ep','Is there anything else you want the Educational Psychologist to know before the assessment?','e.g., the child presents very differently on a good day vs a bad day — please do not base conclusions on a single observation; previous SALT assessment was inconclusive')}
  ${qb('tv_collab','How would you like to work with the EP and other professionals going forward?','e.g., we would welcome joint observation, regular feedback, a post-assessment meeting with parents, and clear recommendations we can implement in setting')}`;
}

